DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Brunetto Latini

who   : Dante's old teacher and mentor.
what  : Among the violent against nature, running forever across the burning sand.
where : Circle VII — Violence against God and nature.
why   : For the sin the poem places him under, though it never stops loving him.
when  : Under the slow rain of fire.
how   : He runs beside his old pupil a little way, and is mourned with real tenderness.

class : Circle VII · Violence · blood, thorn, and burning sand
